import{_ as t,o,c as n,a,d as e,e as r,b as i}from"./app-de7a4551.js";const s={},c=e("h1",{id:"why-your-life-needs-novelty-no-matter-your-age-3",tabindex:"-1"},[e("a",{class:"header-anchor",href:"#why-your-life-needs-novelty-no-matter-your-age-3","aria-hidden":"true"},"#"),r(" Why Your Life Needs Novelty, No Matter Your Age (3)")],-1),d=i('<p>And then you might experience <code>loss</code> or <code>grief</code>.</p><p>And then you enter your 30s and that&#39;s it.</p><p>No more powerful first experiences and life <em>repeats itself</em> over and over.</p><p>Something about that seems so <code>unfulfilling</code>.</p><p>Now imagine if you were a kid from a community like the Bronx.</p><p>While the Bronx offers amazing experiences, by the time you turn 14 or 15, you can feel like you&#39;ve experienced all the powerful first experiences in that environment.</p><p>And so I became <code>obsessed</code> with <em><code>figuring</code> out</em> how to give more powerful first experiences to others.</p><p>My organization, Gentlemen&#39;s <code>Retreat</code>, focuses on young men of color from the inner city who <em>end up</em> going to top colleges and universities, such as Brown University.</p><p>These young men are gifted and they&#39;re special.</p><p>They just felt they <em>experienced everything</em> their community had to offer.</p><p>We call these young men Gs for gentlemen.</p><p>And while working with these gentlemen and giving them powerful first experiences, I realized it was <code>shaping</code> their identities in a <em><code>positive</code> way</em>, but it was also increasing their cultural and their <em>social <code>capital</code></em>.</p><details class="custom-container details"><summary>translation</summary><p><strong>sentence:</strong><br> 然后你会经历失去和伤痛。<br> 然后到了 30 岁，全剧终。<br> 再也没有震撼的第一次，生活一次又一次地反复上演。<br> 这种感觉太没意思了。<br> 想象一下你是一个布朗克斯之类的社区里的小孩。<br> 虽然布朗克斯确实会给你留下一些神奇的经历，但是等你到了 14 或 15 岁,你就会感觉你已经经历过这个环境中所有震撼的第一次了。<br> 我很想知道如何为他人带来更多的震撼的第一次。<br> 我的组织&quot;绅士的静修&quot;（Gentlemen&#39;s Retreat）主要关注内陆城市的有色人种，他们最终在顶尖大学院校就读，如布朗大学。<br> 这些年轻人很有天赋，他们是独特的。<br> 他们感觉自己已经经历过他们的社区可以提供的所有事了。<br> 我们称这些年轻人为&quot;G&quot;，代表&quot;绅士&quot;（Gentlemen）。<br> 和这些绅士合作，给他们带来震撼的第一次，我发现这种方式正以积极的方式塑造着他们的身份，同时也在增加他们的文化和社会资本。</p></details><p>An <code>individual</code> has <em>cultural capital</em> because of the environment that they come from.</p><p>The knowledge, skills and belief of that environment can be seen as capital or an asset.</p><p>And having the <code>combination</code> allows an individual to have <em>economic advantages</em> and other advantages.</p><p>And when you collect powerful first experiences, you&#39;re collecting cultural capital from different environments.</p><p><em>Social capital</em> is a set of <em>shared values</em> and resources that allows individuals to come together to achieve a common goal.</p><p>It can also <em>be thought of</em> as the ability to access resources and <code>favors</code> and information from your network.</p><p><code>Countless</code> connections are <code>fostered</code> when the gentlemen develop <em>intimate relationships</em> in places such as Paris, London and even Montana.</p><p>As they spend time with locals, entrepreneurs and even <em>venture capitalists</em>.</p><p>They develop a more expansive network and idea of the world.</p><p>And increasing cultural and social capital doesn&#39;t just benefit the gentlemen, it also benefits the communities that they <code>bless</code> with their <code>presence</code>.</p><details class="custom-container details"><summary>translation</summary><p><strong>sentence:</strong><br> 人们的文化资本来源于他们出身的环境。<br> 关于这个环境的知识、技能和信仰都可以被视为资本或资产。<br> 有了这些，这个人就有了经济上的优势和其他优势。<br> 如果你去积累震撼的第一次，你就积累了来自不同环境的文化资本。<br> 社会资本指的是一些共享的价值和资源，让人们可以齐心协力达成一个共同的目标。<br> 也可以将其想象成从你的社交网络中获取资源、帮助和信息的能力。<br> 随着这些绅士在巴黎、伦敦，甚至是蒙大拿发展了亲密关系，就建立起了无数联结。<br> 他们和当地人、企业家，甚至是风投共度了时光。<br> 他们形成了更宽广的世界网络和全球视野。<br> 增加文化和社会资本不仅仅会为绅士们带来好处，还会让他们出身的社区受益。</p></details>',24);function l(m,p){return o(),n("div",null,[c,a(" 为什么你的生活需要新奇，无论你的年龄（3）  "),d])}const u=t(s,[["render",l],["__file","24-needs-novelty-3.html.vue"]]);export{u as default};
